    "summary": "I am a senior geologist working on New Ventures Exploration. I am currently the subsurface lead for a venture in West Africa. Skilled in regional to prospect scale analysis while integrating a wide range of data. I bring a specialism in stratigraphy and clastic sedimentology applied from core to outcrop and plate scales. My career at Shell has spanned the Middle East and North Africa, the Indian Ocean and Africa and the South Atlantic, from regional studies to prospect appraisal in new and held ventures. I am a regular reviewer of journal articles and have organised AAPG workshops as part of technical committees. My interests lie in academic and industrial geoscience.\n\nPrior to joining Shell I spent 18 months at Rock Deformation Research Ltd (RDR) where I contributed to the development of content for the Studio Advisor module for Petrel which provides embedded workflows and geological guidance for the Petrel E&P platform. \n\nBefore industry I spent 7 years within the industry funded consortium \"North Africa Research Group\" at the University of Manchester (UK).  The group has a specialism in fieldwork and regional geology throughout North Africa from Morocco to Egypt. During this time I was also able to continue a part time PhD with the group. I was fortunate to study the Numidian Flysch formation in Sicily and northern Tunisia with an aim to piecing together the slope depositional architectures. I also spent time trying to piece together the ambiguous basin evolution including the provenance of the deep marine sediments which remains one of the main controversies within the geology of the western Mediterranean.",
