                    "company": "Shell",
                    "description": "My general responsibilities in Oil and Gas exploration over the last 8 years have focused on;\n\u25cf Managing and interpreting geospatial data including seismic data, gravity and magnetics, Well data including petrophysical logs and biostratigraphic interpretation, and the integration of specialist studies including geochemistry, stable isotopes and fluid inclusion data.\n\u25cf Drawing together of these disparate data types into a coherent story describing the evolution of a basin at a range of scales. Primarily involving the mapping of structures and facies types along with geochemical data and outputs from basin models to provide a view on hydrocarbon prospectivity. \n\u25cf Representing the full uncertainty range in the parameters of geological models and how this impacts the commercial decisions to be taken. Understanding also the statistical chance of failure of the project due to risk and uncertainty.\n\u25cf Managing technical aspects of the team to deliver high quality studies on time and on budget. Being aware of well-being within the team.\n\u25cf Planning a structured approach to projects with framing events, agreement of key deliverables, decision gates to be taken, assurance plans, and stakeholder engagement.\n\u25cf Communicating often complex stories to decision makers in a simple and understandable manner. Supporting decisions involving significant capital expenditure. \n\u25cf Maintaining secure communications with external companies, and honouring restricted or confidential ways of working.\n\u25cf Safety and wellbeing is a key concern where geological understanding of the petroleum system (i.e. reservoir pressures and gasses such as H2S) can put people in potentially harmful situations. I have also attended first aid at work and first aid in the field courses.\n\u25cf I have worked several years in the equatorial West African Atlantic on held ventures as well as new ventures opportunities. I have also worked on projects in Oman, Bulgaria/Romania, across north Africa and the Indian sub-continent.",
